# Static-host HTTP response headers (Netlify / Cloudflare Pages `_headers` format).
# These deliver protections that a <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy">
# tag cannot enforce (frame-ancestors, X-Frame-Options are header-only).
# For hosts that do not read `_headers` (nginx, Apache, Vercel, S3/CloudFront),
# replicate the same headers in that host's config.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'none'
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
